â­ PART 3 â€” JavaScript Explanation

JavaScript adds interactivity and animations.

Your JavaScript has 4 major functions:

ğŸš€ 1. Smooth Scrolling for Navigation Links
Code:
document.querySelectorAll('a[href^="#"]').forEach(anchor => {
    anchor.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
        e.preventDefault();
        const target = document.querySelector(this.getAttribute('href'));
        if (target) {
            target.scrollIntoView({
                behavior: 'smooth',
                block: 'start'
            });
        }
    });
});

Function:

When you click on Home, Features, Reviews, Download, the page scrolls smoothly instead of jumping.

This improves user experience.

ğŸš€ 2. Scroll to Download Section (Button Action)
Code:
function scrollToDownload() {
    document.getElementById('download').scrollIntoView({
        behavior: 'smooth'
    });
}

Function:

When user clicks â€œGet Startedâ€, it automatically scrolls to the download section.

ğŸš€ 3. Scroll Reveal Animation (Intersection Observer)
Code:
const observer = new IntersectionObserver(function(entries) {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
            entry.target.style.opacity = '1';
            entry.target.style.transform = 'translateY(0)';
        }
    });
}, observerOptions);

Function:

This code reveals feature cards and testimonials when they appear on the screen.

Cards start:

Hidden (opacity 0)

Pushed down (translateY(20px))

When visible â†’ they fade in and move up smoothly.

Makes the website modern and animated.

ğŸš€ 4. Change Header Background on Scroll
Code:
window.addEventListener('scroll', function() {
    const header = document.querySelector('header');
    if (window.scrollY > 100) {
        header.style.background = 'rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.95)';
    } else {
        header.style.background = 'linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%)';
    }
});

Function:

When the user scrolls down:

Header becomes solid (more visible)
When user is at top:

Original gradient is restored

Helps readability and improves design.

